      "content": "that sounds a bit generic though... like, if i'm being honest, when people think of \"urban\" style, they usually have a specific look in mind. like, what kind of people or specific communities are we actually talking about here? i don't want to just do \"utility\" and \"grayscale\" and miss the actual soul of what makes it urban. what are the key visual markers tied to the actual people who created this style?",
